# Cursor Rules — HESEM MOM ERP

## CRITICAL: File Placement
Before creating any file, read `.ai/CONVENTIONS.md`.
NEVER place files at the repo root (exceptions: CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, index.html, index.php, robots.txt, favicon.ico, dotfiles).

## Project Navigation
- Read `.ai/repo-map.json` first for project orientation
- Find a table's domain: Grep `.ai/db-map/index.json`, then read `.ai/db-map/<domain>.json`
- Find a class/method: Grep `.ai/symbols.json` (do NOT read the full file)
- Domain business rules: `.ai/module-summaries/<domain>.md`
- Full protocol: `CLAUDE.md`

## Stack
- PHP 8.2+, PostgreSQL, Redis, RabbitMQ — no framework
- Entry: `mom/api/index.php`, autoload: `mom/composer.json` (PSR-4)
- Namespaces: `MOM\Api\Controllers\`, `MOM\Api\Services\`, `MOM\Database\`
- Data layer: JSON_ONLY → SHADOW_WRITE → POSTGRES_PRIMARY → POSTGRES_ONLY

## Code Rules
- `declare(strict_types=1)` on every PHP file
- `final class` for all services and controllers
- Always provide fallbacks: try infrastructure → catch Throwable → file fallback → log
- No framework rewrites. No microservices without scaling justification.
- Production write paths: role-guarded, auditable, least-privilege

## Where files go (quick reference)
- AI prompt docs → `mom/docs/ai-prompts/`
- Architecture specs → `docs/architecture/`
- Security audits → `docs/audits/`
- QMS standards → `standards/`
- Build scripts → `tools/scripts/<category>/`
- Generated reports → `_reports/<category>/`
- PHP controllers → `mom/api/controllers/`
- PHP services → `mom/api/services/`
- SQL migrations → `mom/database/migrations/`
